---
// "About the name" — lifted out of the converted WordPress prose into a designed
// block, because it is the one bit of the About page people actually quote back.
// wp-export cuts the original section from about.md so the two cannot drift.
---

<section class="name-origin" data-reveal>
  <div class="kicker">// about the name</div>

  <div class="wordmark">
    <span class="m">m</span><span class="it">IT</span><span class="m">y</span><span class="dot">.</span><span class="m">John</span>
  </div>

  <div class="phonetic">
    <span class="ipa">/ˈmaɪti dʒɒn/</span>
    <span class="say">say it like &ldquo;mighty john&rdquo;</span>
  </div>

  <div class="breakdown">
    <div class="bit">
      <span class="bit-key">sounds like</span>
      <span class="bit-val">mighty</span>
    </div>
    <div class="bit">
      <span class="bit-key">contains</span>
      <span class="bit-val it">IT</span>
      <span class="bit-note">Information Technology, the bit that pays the rent</span>
    </div>
    <div class="bit">
      <span class="bit-key">John</span>
      <span class="bit-val">= Jan</span>
      <span class="bit-note">English for my Dutch name, a nod to anyone outside Belgium</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="closer">
    No, you don&rsquo;t have to spell it out letter by letter. If you ever hesitate,
    just say it like a superhero with a laptop.
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .name-origin {
    margin: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px) 0;
    padding: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 38px) clamp(20px, 3vw, 34px);
    background: linear-gradient(140deg, var(--s2), var(--s1));
    border: 1px solid var(--border2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-panel);
  }
  .kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-caps);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  /* the wordmark, with the IT actually doing the shouting */
  .wordmark {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(34px, 6vw, 60px);
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .wordmark .it {
    color: var(--accent);
    position: relative;
  }
  /* underline only under the IT */
  .wordmark .it::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: -6px;
    height: 3px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    background: var(--accent);
  }
  .wordmark .dot { color: var(--accent); }

  .phonetic {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 20px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-small);
  }
  .ipa {
    color: var(--text);
    border: 1px solid var(--border3);
    border-radius: var(--radius-btn-sm);
    padding: 4px 10px;
  }
  .say { color: var(--muted2); }

  .breakdown {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(190px, 1fr));
    gap: 14px;
    margin-top: 26px;
  }
  .bit {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    background: var(--bg2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
  }
  .bit-key {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-caption-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted2);
  }
  .bit-val {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .bit-val.it { color: var(--accent); }
  .bit-note {
    font-size: var(--text-small);
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .closer {
    margin: 22px 0 0;
    font-size: var(--text-body-lg);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 62ch;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
</style>
